# Used for production builds (`pnpm build`) only. `vite dev` sets baseURL to "" so the browser calls
# `/api` on the same host as the app (e.g. localhost:5173) and Vite proxies to the API — that keeps
# the refresh cookie first-party. If you build with VITE_API_URL pointing at another origin, the
# httpOnly refresh cookie is stored for THAT host (e.g. localhost:3001), not for :5173.
#
# The refresh token is NEVER in Local Storage / Session Storage. It is cookie `refresh_token`
# (httpOnly). Check DevTools → Application → Cookies → the exact origin in the address bar (e.g.
# http://localhost:5173). If `POST /api/auth/sso/callback` never returns 200, that cookie is not set.
#
# VITE_DEV_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:3001
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
